  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide immediate life-saving Food Assistance to 115,700 people affected by IDAI cyclone and floods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this WFP project is to provide lifesaving food assistance for one month to the population affected by Cyclone Idai in Mozambique. With this CERF grant, WFP will procure and distribute 1,857 tons of food. WFP will also establish a complaints report mechanism through a contractor for a value of USD96,500. The project will last six months and will benefit 117,700 people including 21,983 women and 34,710 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
